Notes: This column likely represents a unique identifier for the prescription record, aligning with the 'hasIdentifier' property of the main entity.
Patient ID is a key demographic identifier, best mapped via the 'hasPatient' relationship from the prescription to the patient entity.
ATC code corresponds to the drug's classification, mapped through the 'hasDrug' relationship to the Drug entity.
Diagnosis code indicates the medical condition for indication, linked via 'hasIndicationToStart' to the Diagnosis entity.
The creation date records the timestamp of the prescription event, mapped directly to the 'hasDateTime' property with datetime datatype.
Number of times per day indicates frequency, mapped through 'hasFrequency' link to Quantity, representing dosing frequency.
Dosage details are best captured via 'hasDrugQuantity', which can include value and unit for precise dosage information.
